icy, and organization and management are discussed, as are front-line service delivery, service provider work environments, and the realities of daily living for families. Informed by recent research, the contributors provide clear directions for policy, administration, and service-delivery reforms. Informing policy debates addressing child maltreatment and family welfare, this book will serve as a vital resource for managers, service providers, professionals, and students in the fields of social work, child and youth care, family studies, psychology, and special education.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChild welfarexCanada. 0aChild welfarezCanada. 0aEnfantsxProtection, assistance, etcxCanada. 0aFamille, Services à laxCanada. 0aFamily servicesxCanada. 0aFamily serviceszCanada. 0aFamily social workxCanada. 0aFamily social workzCanada. 0aService social aux enfantsxCanada. 0aService social familialxCanadaxKanadaxCanada. 0aSocial work with childrenxCanada. 0aSocial work with childrenzCanada. 4aLaw: Child Advocacy. 4aPolitical Science: Social Policy. 4aSocial Science: Social Work. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh1 aAdams, Gerald R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAdams, Gerald R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBlackstock, Cindy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCameron, Gary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCameron, Gary, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCarlson, Joyce Clouston, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoady, Nick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoady, Nick, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCorn